    page6: "A helpful trick: practice one short vowel word family at a time, like -at, -en, -ig, -og, and -ug, until each sound feels automatic.",
    page7: "You reviewed all five short vowel sounds — a, e, i, o, u — and how to identify them in words like cat, hen, pig, dog, and bug."
