    page6: "A helpful trick: many collective nouns are fun and unique, like a 'murder' of crows or a 'pod' of dolphins — learning a few is like learning secret words.",
    page7: "You learned to use collective nouns, special group words like school (fish), herd (cows), and pack (wolves)."
